attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, too large section header offset jd

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is classified as malicious, exhibiting characteristics of a Linux botnet (likely a Mirai variant). It contains over 24,000 strings, many of which appear to be obfuscated or fragmented machine code fragments. Significant IOCs include fragmented paths targeting '/proc/self/' and '/etc/local', which are typically used by malware for self-identification and persistence. The lack of standard imports/sections and the presence of high-entropy string templates (e.g., '9Y8wwrbJi-...') further indicate packing and obfuscation used to hinder static analysis.
